All Koreans Called Upon to Ostracize GNP 
e082401 - All Koreans Called Upon to Ostracize GNP 

&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 24 (KCNA) -- The Secretariat of the Committee for the Peaceful Reunification of the Fatherland in Information Bulletin No. 845 issued on August 23 lashed out at the Grand National Party of south Korea for working hard to deteriorate the situation and totally block national reconciliation and unity, far from feeling responsible for what it did on August 15 to seriously affect the development of the inter-Korean relations. 
 Riff-raffs of the GNP are now hurling malignant abuses on the authorities, claiming that it was "wrong" for them to have apologized to the north for the anti-north rowdyism perpetrated by ultra-right conservative forces on the August 15 liberation day, the bulletin noted, and continued: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The August 15 incident was a wicked political provocation as it triggered off unbearable resentment among our people and the servicemen of the People's Army and a rash action against the nation and reunification as it was intended to ditch the June 15 joint declaration and bedevil the inter-Korean relations. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The reality goes to prove that unless the moves of the GNP and other ultra-right conservative forces are decisively frustrated, they will hamstring the process of national reconciliation and unity and seriously affect the movement for the peace and reunification of the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It called upon the people from all walks of life in south Korea to come out in a struggle for completely ostracizing the group of traitors.

Seminar on Kim Jong Il's Work Held in Egypt 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 24 (KCNA) -- A seminar on leader Km Jong Il's famous work "Let Us Give Fuller Play to the Advantages of Our People's Power" was held by the Egyptian Committee for the Study of the Juche Idea on Aug. 12.
 The work, published on December 21, Juche 81 (1992), comprehensively indicated the principle, tasks and ways of building the people's power to the world progressives striving to defend the cause of socialism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Yehia Zakariya Khairallah, chairman of the committee, in a speech said that President Kim Il Sung was the most distinguished political elder and benevolent father of the people, who fathered the Juche idea, built a genuine people's power in Korea and pursued a policy for the people all his life. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that while staying in the DPRK he saw for himself the Korean people fully enjoying a happy life, singleheartedly united around the Party and the leader, he stressed that  Kim Jong Il who is steadfastly carrying forward the President's revolutionary cause is the sun of the 21st century, the most outstanding thinker and theoretician and the people's father as he has further strengthened the people's power with his unique Songun revolutionary leadership. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He expressed belief that under his Songun leadership the Korean people would certainly build a great prosperous and powerful nation and reunify the country in the near future.

Koreans Called upon to Achieve Great National Unity 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 24 (KCNA) -- All Koreans should turn out as one in the struggle to foil the U.S. imperialists' moves for a war and thus protect the peace and security of the country and the sovereignty and the vital rights of the nation, says Rodong Sinmun today in a signed article.
 It is high time that all the Koreans in the north, south and abroad achieved great unity and turned out in a vigorous struggle to foil the U.S. arrogant moves now that the danger of a war is increasing on the Korean peninsula as the days go by due to their arrogant moves, the article says, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Koreans in the north, south and abroad should closely unite as one to resolutely foil the U.S. imperialists' moves for a war. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Koreans should neither hesitate nor waver in the way of achieving the national unity because of differing ideologies, systems, political views, religious beliefs, classes and strata. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
All the Koreans should face up to the reality today when the destiny of the nation is exposed to a grave threat due to the U.S. imperialist warhawks' moves to provoke a war and turn out as one for national unity to cope with it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Flunkeyism and the idea of depending on outsiders should be rejected and a positive struggle should be waged against the traitors to the nation so as to protect the peace of the country and the security of the nation from the U.S. imperialists' war moves. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Koreans in the north, south and abroad should have the transparent stand for national independence that the nation alone can solve the issue of achieving the peace of the country and the security of the nation and resolutely reject such flunkeyist idea of relying on outside forces as leaving the nation's destiny to their tender mercy or begging them to shape it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean nation should further strengthen solidarity and cooperation in the struggle to foil the U.S. imperialists' criminal moves for aggression. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Koreans in the north, south and abroad should protect peace and security of the country with the might of great national unity to meet the requirements of the prevailing situation and escalate the movement for national reunification.

Anti-DPRK War Moves of U.S. and S. Korea Flailed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 23 (KCNA) -- The Secretariat of the Committee for the Peaceful Reunification of the Fatherland made public information bulletin No. 844 on August 22, vehemently condemning the U.S. and south Korea for resorting to war moves against the DPRK behind the smoke-screen of dialogue.
 According to the information bulletin, the U.S. hawks are seeking dangerous military movements by saying that both south Korea and the U.S. should provide against the second war on the Korean peninsula including military attacks though the opening of the six-way talks was agreed upon. They, together with the south Korean army, are launching the dangerous Ulji Focus Lens joint military exercise throughout south Korea from August 18 to 29. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. is still persisting in all sorts of war provocation moves against the DPRK, which clearly shows that their clamors for "assurance of peace" or "talks" are a sheer lie and that through the six-way talks they are seeking to disarm the DPRK completely and, in case it is impossible, to control it by force of arms, the information bulletin stressed, and added: If the U.S. takes the road of war against the north behind the curtain of dialogue, not withdrawing its hostile policy towards the DPRK, we will never give up nuclear deterrent force and settle accounts with the aggressors. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. should not commit a rash act, seeing the will of our army and people to annihilate the enemies. The south Korean authorities, too, should not dance to the tune of the U.S. war to hamstring the nation but come out to national cooperation for removing the danger of a war and defending peace.

British Association for Study of Songun Policy Formed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 23 (KCNA) -- The British Association for the Study of the Songun Policy was formed with due ceremony in London on Aug. 16.
 On display in the venue of the ceremony were a photograph of leader Kim Jong Il making a field inspection of a unit of the Korean People's Army and books and photos on the vitality of the Songun policy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Dermot Hudson, vice-chairman of the British Friendship Society with Korea and chief of the British Group for the Study of the Juche Idea and Works of Comrade Kim Jong Il, was elected chairman of the association. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He in a speech at the ceremony noted that members of the association would make positive efforts to introduce the essence, validity and vitality of the Songun policy set forth by  Kim Jong Il to the people from all walks of life through Internet. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The ceremony decided to send a letter to Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there were Andy Brooks, general secretary of the Central Committee of the New Communist Party of Great Britain, Christopher Coleman, spokesman (leader) of the Central Committee of the Revolutionary Communist Party of Britain (Marxist-Leninist), Keith Bennett, chairman of the Britain-Korea Friendship and Solidarity Movement, and others.

Australia Urged to Stop Supporting U.S. Hostile Policy towards DPRK 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 23 (KCNA) -- The Communist Party of Australia published an appeal to the Australian people in the Aug. 13 issue of the newspaper Guardian.
 The appeal urged the Australian government to stop supporting the United States in posing a provocative threat to the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. and Australian governments are telling a lie about the DPRK just as they lied about Iraq's weapons of mass destruction, it noted, and continued: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Communist Party of Australia calls on all the Australians to make every possible effort to prevent another war. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We hold that the Australians should not provide fund to the U.S. and Australia preparing a war against the DPRK and other countries.

Book on DPRK Published in Italy
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 23 (KCNA) -- The book "The Democratic People's Republic of Korea is a people's sovereign power" was published by an organization of atheists believing in dialectical materialism of Italy on Aug. 18.
 Noting that the DPRK is a sovereign power that defends the interests and dignity of the country and the nation, the book continued: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 President Kim Il Sung resolutely rejected the interference of foreign forces in the revolution and construction on the principle of the Juche idea. He adhered to the principle of self-defense in national defence, holding aloft the banner of independence against imperialism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Chairman of the DPRK National Defence Commission Kim Jong Il is now pursuing the Songun policy in the DPRK as a successor to the cause of the President. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Under his wise leadership, the DPRK will remain shining forever as a people's sovereign power.

DPRK Women's Soccer Team Beats German Team
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Taegu, August 22 (KCNA-Correspondent) -- The DPRK women's soccer team beat the German team 6:0 in the preliminary match of the 22nd Universiad on August 22.
 The first goal came at the around 8th minute of the match when center forward Ri Un Sim strongly kicked into the rival's goal the ball passed by midfielder Mun Chol Mi from the leftside of the scoring area. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 And its second goal came at the 10th minute of the match when Mun Chol Mi made a strong penalty kick from an area 16 meters from the opponent's goal and the ball was netted after touching the rival team goalkeeper's hand &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The team scored the third goal 17 minutes before the end of the first half of the match when forward Kim Yong Ae kicked the ball into the net.
 One more goal was scored by midfielder Kim Kyong Hwa at the around 10th minute of the second half of the match and then two more goals were won by back So Chun Myong. The match thus ended 6:0. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 12 teams including the DPRK women's soccer team will have league matches in four groups and a winner and a runner-up in each group will hold a tournament.

Rodong Sinmun on Illegal U.S. Military Presence in S. Korea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 23 (KCNA) -- The U.S. imperialist aggressor troops' occupation was illegal and brigandish as it had no justification in view of international law, says Rodong Sinmun in an article today.
 The Cairo talks in November 1943 stipulated that Korea should be a sovereign and independent country and the Moscow meeting of foreign ministers of three countries in December 1945 adopted as an international convention a decision that called for eliminating the 38th parallel and establishing a democratic sovereign and independent state in Korea, but the United States nullified the decision and occupied south Korea on September 8, 1945, in pursuance of its criminal policy of domination over Korea, the article says, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The continued U.S. military presence in south Korea is a wanton violation of the Korean Armistice Agreement. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Paragraph 60 of Article IV of the AA stipulates that within three (3) months after the Armistice Agreement is signed and becomes effective, a political conference of a higher level of both sides be held by representatives appointed respectively to settle through negotiation the questions of the withdrawal of all foreign forces from Korea, etc. The U.S. imperialists laid an artificial stumbling block in the way of the negotiation to be held in accordance with the article to foil it on purpose, though. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The AA remains dead as a dodo on the Korean peninsula. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. keeps its military presence in south Korea in utter disregard of a resolution of the UN General Assembly. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All the facts clearly prove that Yanks are the aggressors who are desperately keeping the Koreans from independently reunifying the country and posing a grave threat to peace and security in the peninsula, Asia and the rest of the world and a group of devils defying the UN Charter, international law and world public opinion. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. should be mindful that its unabated efforts to aggravate the situation in the peninsula will lead itself to helpless self-destruction and act with discretion and pull its aggression forces out of south Korea at once.

National Educational Program Exhibition Held
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 23 (KCNA) -- The 4th National Educational Program Exhibition was held in Pyongyang from Aug. 19 to 22.
 On display there were more than 450 successful programs including over 100 computer-aided educational programs developed by teachers, researchers and students of Kim Il Sung University, Kim Chaek University of Technology, University of Science, Kanggye University of Technology, Nampho University of Fisheries and other universities, colleges and middle schools in the past one year. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Highly appreciated were such programs as geographical information system "Samcholli" presented by Kim Il Sung University, and programs for industrial management developed by Kim Chaek University of Technology, University of Science and other universities, a program for the study of analytics by Kim Hyong Jik University of Education and multi-media program "We Are One" by Pyongyang Kaeson Middle School No. 1. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A closing ceremony of the exhibition took place at the Three Revolution Exhibition on Aug. 22. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Citations and prizes were awarded to successful participants at the ceremony.

6th National Taekwon-Do Championships for Jongilbong Cup Held
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 23 (KCNA) -- The 6th National Taekwon-Do Championships for Jongilbong Cup was held at the Taekwon-Do Hall from Aug. 18 to 22.
 Participating in the championships were over 620 men and women players selected from among provincial (municipality) Taekwon-Do schools (including adult class) and the team (training group) of the Korean Taekwon-Do Committee. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 There were team and individual matches of sparring, pattern and special techniques, divided into junior and adult classes. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The North Hwanghae Provincial Taekwon-Do School Team came first in total, picking up 9 gold medals in different events of junior class, and the South Phyongan Provincial Taekwon-Do School Team placed first in total in adult class events. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the closing ceremony of the championships on Aug. 22 trophy cups and medals were awarded to the best teams and players and technical prizes to the players who displayed high techniques and refined and powerful special movements.
